21st Inter-Korean Ministerial Talks Open 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Seoul, May 30 (KCNA correspondent) -- The 21st North-South Ministerial Talks opened in Seoul on Wednesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were members of the north side's delegation led by Chief Councilor of the DPRK Cabinet Kwon Ho Ung and its suite members and delegates of the south side with Minister of Unification Ri Jae Jong as chief delegate and its suite members. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The head of the north side's delegation and the south side's chief delegate made speeches at the talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kwon analyzed the experience and lesson, reviewing how the inter-Korean ministerial talks proceeded, before advancing proposals reflecting the principled stand of the north side to firmly preserve and thoroughly implement the idea of "By our nation itself".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He underscored the need to abide by the principle of settling the issues related to the inter-Korean relations from the stand of attaching importance to the nation and placing it above anything else. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recalling that the implementation of the points agreed between the north and the south is held up due to the outside forces' interference and relations with outside forces are considered more important than the inter-Korean relations, he called for implementing to the letter the agreed points reflecting the interests and wishes of the nation on the principle of attaching importance to the nation and placing it above anything else. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He also underlined the need to take decisive measures against the occurrence of any acts of provoking the other dialogue partner and endangering the inter-Korean relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He referred to the fact that there have been a chain of abnormal developments running counter to the main spirit of the June 15 Joint Declaration since the 20th inter-Korean ministerial talks as evidenced by the north-targeted military exercises staged by the south side together with outside forces and a spate of insolent remarks let loose by its authorities including the prime minister to slander the ideology and system in the DPRK and even negate its sovereignty and inviolable territory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Deploring that one can hardly witness the implementation of the agreed points related to such fundamental and principled matters as matters of taking practical measures to ensure that each other's ideology and system are recognized and respected, he declared that in that context it is advisable for the current talks to focus the discussion on settling the fundamental points already agreed rather than working to make new agreements. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The talks go on.

Withdrawal of U.S. Imperialists from S. Korea Urged 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 30 (KCNA) -- Organizations in the U.S. and Britain sent solidarity messages to the Pyongyang mission of the Anti-Imperialist National Democratic Front (AINDF) on May 20 and 21 on the occasion of the 27th anniversary of the heroic Kwangju Popular Uprising. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. Group for the Study of Songun Politics and the U.S. Solidarity Committee to Support the Struggle of AINDF and the South Korean People in their messages extended support to the south Korean people in their struggle for justice and patriotism on the occasion of the 27th anniversary of the uprising. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The British Group for the Study of the Juche Idea and the British Association for the Study of Songun Policy in their messages said the uprising was a heroic resistance to shine long in the history of the world oppressed people's struggle for national liberation as it dealt a heavy blow at the U.S. imperialist aggressors. The messages called for driving the hateful U.S. imperialists out of south Korea.

Kim Jong Il's Policy on Science and Technology Praised in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 30 (KCNA) -- The south Korean Internet magazine "Jongse Tonghyang" on May 23 posted an article titled "Chairman of the National Defence Commission Kim Jong Il builds a great prosperous powerful nation by attaching great importance to science and technology" written by Jon Yong Ho, permanent researcher of the south Korean Institute for Civic Rights Studies. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The article had the following five parts: "1. Chairman of NDC Kim Jong Il giving great importance to science and technology", "2. The policy of giving great importance to science and technology, a continuation of President Kim Il Sung's policy", "3. Information communication, Nano-engineering, life engineering", "4. Methodology of developing science and technology" and "5. Future of the north's science and technology".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The article noted that Kim Jong Il regarded science and technology as one of the three mainstays for building a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The President's policy of giving importance to science and technology has been carried forward by Kim Jong Il to bring about signal innovations in all fields of science and technology as evidenced by the launch of an earth satellite and the successful nuclear test, the article noted, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Sustained state attention has been paid to the field of science and technology in the north, demonstrating its various scientific and technological achievements at home and abroad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The north's science and technology in the 21st century guarantee a preferential development of the national defence industry and progress in the main fields of the national economy including power, coal, metal and railways, the article said, adding that "the north is expected to keep science and technology ahead of other fields to bolster armed forces for self-defence and develop the national economy."

Senior Official of China Meets Korean Women's Delegation 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Beijing, May 28 (KCNA) -- Gu Xiulian, vice-chairwoman of the Standing Committee of the Chinese National People's Congress who is president of the All-China Women's Federation, met and had a talk with a delegation of the Korean Democratic Women's Union led by Vice-Chairwoman Ro Song Sil at the Great Hall of the People in Beijing on Monday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Gu Xiulian said she was happy to note that the 95th birth anniversary of President Kim Il Sung was commemorated with splendor in Korea. I was deeply moved to see the Korean people deeply revering the President, she added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that when she visited Korea last year she was greatly encouraged by the achievements made in different fields of it under the leadership of Kim Jong Il, she hoped that the Korean people would register greater success in the future, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were the vice-president of the All-China Women's Federation, and Choe Jin Su, DPRK ambassador to China.

GNP's Political Repression Denounced in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 30 (KCNA) -- The Solidarity for Implementing the South-North Joint Declaration in south Korea on May 25 released a statement titled "The Grand National Party should stop its suppression of the just political activities of civic organizations", according to a media report. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement recalled that the GNP filed a suit with the prosecution against the core members of the Solidarity including Permanent Co-Representative Kwon O Chang for a street oratorical meeting against it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the anti-national and anti-reunification acts of the GNP have become an object of curse and denunciation by all the people, the statement said the GNP, nevertheless, is suppressing the righteous political activities of a civic organization, crying over what it called "defamation".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The incident vividly revealed the wild ambition of the GNP to take power at any cost through the "presidential election" by blindfolding the people and stuffing their ears, the statement said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It declared that the civic organizations would never stop their fight against the GNP.

Japan's Scenario of Preemptive Attack under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 30 (KCNA) -- Japan has been very busy boosting the military capability of the "Self-Defence Forces (SDF)" under the signboard of "defence" these years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson Wednesday in a signed commentary carried in this regard terms it hysteria intended to mount preemptive attacks on other countries as it pleases. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is evidenced by its frantic moves to build MD. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan is now accelerating the MD deployment with PAC-3 and SM-3 for Aegis as its main components. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As if it were not enough with this, Japan decided to start the research and development of high-performance laser weapons in a bid to intercept missiles right after their launch. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries are rapidly converting not only strategic weapons but conventional ones into weaponry of offensive nature. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is quite obvious that the SDF is emerging aggressor armed forces of offensive nature and Japan a war state. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japan Defense Agency was upgraded to the Ministry of Defence and a new central rapid reaction force was created while Japan is posed to exercise the "right to collective self-defence" in contravention of its Constitution. One can hardly interpret this development as for "defence". An offensive formula would be the only correct explanation of the moves of Japan to emerge a military power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Now is the time for the world community to take a serious note of Japan's dangerous moves for militaristic overseas expansion that have reached an alarming phase and take a responsible action against them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK will never allow the scenario of the Japanese reactionaries for a preemptive attack in order to ensure peace and security in Asia and the rest of the world, the commentary concludes.

U.S. Double-dealing Policy Accused 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 30 (KCNA) -- The United States should roll back its unjustifiable double-dealing policy and hostile policy toward the DPRK if it is truly interested in the settlement of the nuclear and missile issues, urges Rodong Sinmun Wednesday in a signed commentary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Disclosing the U.S. recent moves to round off the preparations for a nuclear war and its intensified military tie-up with Japan, the news analyst goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What should not be overlooked is the U.S. double-dealing policy. The Japanese reactionaries are working hard to establish the Missile Defence System (MD) while pushing forward the moves to become a military giant with the backing of the U.S. and at its connivance. Accession to nuclear weapons by Israel and other countries is chiefly attributable to the U.S. connivance and cooperation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The nuclear issue of the DPRK, however, originated from the U.S. nuclear threat toward it. But for the U.S. escalated nuclear threat to the DPRK its nuclear issue would not have cropped up. The U.S., proceeding from its double-dealing stand, found fault with the DPRK only, while defending and supporting Israel and other countries in their nuclear weaponization and cooperating with them. This is a revelation of its extreme two-faced policy and one-sided hostile policy toward the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such countries as the U.S. and Japan say this or that about the measure taken by the DPRK for increasing its defence capacity although they manufacture latest type nuclear weapons and missiles of the next generation as they please. This double-dealing policy should not be tolerated under any circumstances. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is self-evident that the nuclear and missile issues can hardly be settled fairly as long as countries like the U.S. cling to their double-dealing policy. The persistent application of double-dealing standards would reduce even international law and treaties to dead papers.

Japan's Trick to Evade Responsibility for Past Crimes Debunked
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 30 (KCNA) -- It is a mockery and insult to human conscience for Japan to attempt to participate in the activities of the International Criminal Court (ICC) dealing with such anti-human crimes as genocide and aggression, states Rodong Sinmun in a commentary Wednesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan is these days trying to cover up the extra-large anti-human crimes, which were and will be unparalleled in history, by craftily abusing the limitation codified in the rules of the ICC that it shall exercise jurisdiction only over the crimes committed in the 21st century, notes the analyst, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan's attempt to involve itself in the activities of the ICC is a crafty move to evade the settlement of its past. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan is wielding its purse to enter the ICC and grab such leading posts of the court as judge. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 But it is mistaken. Money is not a panacea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is unseemly and ironical for such war criminal state as Japan which is destitute of conscience and morality to attempt to join the ICC and discuss international law and judge anti-human crimes. Whatever thick silk dress Japan may wear, it cannot deodorize the stink of crimes from its body. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It must never be allowed that the bloody past crimes of Japan are rinsed out by such international organizations as the ICC. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan should make a new start after fully atoning for the past crimes it committed against humankind before uttering such words as "peace" and "domination of law".

All Koreans Called upon to Achieve National Independence
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 30 (KCNA) -- National independence serves as a main principle to be adhered to in achieving Korea's reunification as it is the core of the issue of reunification, says Rodong Sinmun today in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A solution to the issue of national reunification aimed at defending and realizing independence of the nation would be unthinkable without national independence, the article notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Every nation is entitled to be responsible for its destiny and carve it out according to its own will. Koreans should achieve the reunification of the country by themselves free from any interference of foreign forces. Only then is it possible to successfully resolve the issue of reunification according to the desire and interests of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If one tries to solve the issue of national reunification, an issue of winning back the sovereignty of the nation usurped by foreign forces, in reliance upon foreign forces, it would only end up finding oneself under the yoke of slavery. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The issue of Korea's reunification pertaining to the Korean nation's right to self-determination can be successfully solved only through its concerted efforts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 For the divided Korean nation national independence precisely means reunification and vice versa. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The historic Pyongyang summit and the adoption of the June 15 joint declaration ushered in an era of independent reunification, the first of its kind in the nation's history of the reunification movement. This was a shining fruition of the protracted struggle of the Koreans to achieve the reunification of the country independently. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What is important for the north and the south to achieve national independence at present is to firmly maintain the stand of attaching importance to the nation. This stand precisely represents national independence and its principle can be implemented only when the above-said stand is maintained. Koreans can achieve genuine national reconciliation and accelerate the independent reunification only when they always place the will and interests of the nation above anything else and protect them and remain true to the principle of national independence under any situation and circumstances.

Development of Indigenous National Cooking Culture
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 30 (KCNA) -- The Korean people have developed indigenous national cooking culture, making dishes good for existence, health and longevity of human being since olden times. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They have lived on boiled rice, soy, bean paste and kimchi as the main staple and subsidiary food, proceeding from their experience and general knowledge, though the metabolism of human body had not been solved in a scientific way. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people took in varied nutritive substances and energy from the boiled rice (rice and cereals), the amino acids from the bean paste and pickled fish and vitamins A and C and iron from kimchi. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kimchi, fermentation food, which has been approved as a health food in the world is a product of the Korean women's wisdom. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is just the Korean women who developed various kinds of kimchi according to the taste of each family and each people with raw materials, by properly mixing spice, fishes, pickled fish, fruits and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They have used soybean in the dietary life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They have made bean processed foodstuffs to take nutritive elements like those of meat.  Among bean foodstuffs are various kinds of bean paste, favorite food of the Korean nation, tubu (bean-curds), bean sprouts, and piji (bean-curd dregs). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Finding out that water is helpful to metabolism of the human body and health, they also have developed the dishes mixed with water including cold noodle dish, fish porridge, gray mullet soup, tongchimi (radishes pickled in salt water), parsely kimchi and bouilli of chicken with insam inside. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They widely use edible herbs of medicinal value in the dietary life and make various kinds dishes with internal organs and hocks of domestic animals. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The folk dishes are further encouraged in Korea today.

Korean People Enjoy Benefits from Government
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 30 (KCNA) -- It is the policy of the Workers' Party of Korea and DPRK government to constantly promote the well-being of the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people are leading an independent and creative life, enjoying public benefits thanks to the policies of the Party and government. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the policies are based on the principle of conducting all the activities with the popular masses as the centre. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The word "people" is included in names of the country, power body and monumental edifices including the Grand People's Study House and People's Palace of Culture. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Conspicuous are cultural and welfare facilities for the people everywhere in the country.  Sanatoriums, recuperation homes and rest centres for the working people and camps for schoolchildren are seen in spa and scenic places. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people enjoy the benefits of free medical care and free education.  The tax system has long been abolished completely in the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Party and government take warm care of the life of the aged and children who have no one to depend on and direct preferentiality to the disabled soldiers and persons of merits in the society. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Enormous are the social benefits including the maternity leave and recuperation and rest system for working people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nevertheless, the imperialists are spreading illusion about capitalism, loudly talking about "welfare policy" and "welfare society" in an attempt to collapse the Korean-style socialist system. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people, who are taking their socialism as life-line, are striving to glorify their country as one of the people, decisively frustrating the moves of the imperialists with its superiority.

Cuban, Indonesian Embassy Officials Help Korean Farmers
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 30 (KCNA) -- Ruben Perez Valdes, Cuban ambassador to the DPRK, and his embassy officials helped farmers of the DPRK-Cuba Friendship Hwasong Co-op Farm in removing young rice plants from seedbeds while Daulat Hotma Audison Passaribu, Indonesian ambassador to the DPRK, and his embassy officials farmers of the DPRK-Indonesia Friendship Yaksu Co-op Farm in Kangso County in weeding a maize field on Wednesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They looked round rooms dedicated to the history of the farms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During breaks the officials of the embassies talked and sang together with farmers, deepening the friendship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They handed aid materials to them.

Profound Love and Total Dedication to Country Called for
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 30 (KCNA) -- Love and dedication to the socialist motherland can be most ardent, genuine and lasting only when it is based on human ethics and morality, says Rodong Sinmun Wednesday in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Korean-style socialism is indestructible as the popular masses are united close in thinking and will as well as in the sense of moral obligation, the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Human ethics and morality provide a mental foundation which makes it possible to firmly defend Korean-style socialism in any adversity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the greatest honor, pride and moral obligation for the Korean people to defend their socialist system at the cost of their lives as it provides them with the most worthwhile and dignified life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Neither blockade and sanctions nor reactionary ideological and cultural poisoning and psychological warfare can ever bring the people to their knees because they regard it as their noble moral obligation to defend their own ideology, cause and system. All the Korean people value their socialist country dearer than their lives and defend it at the cost of their lives despite whatever hardships. This provides a sure guarantee for the eternal victory of Korean-style socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Human ethics and morality also serve as a foundation which makes it possible to display to the full the advantages of Korean-style socialism that considers collectivism as its lifeline. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The leader trusts the army and people regarding them as comrades who would accompany him along the long road of revolution and the army and people uphold the leader out of pure conscience holding him in high esteem as their benevolent father and teacher. This is the true picture of Korean-style socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A full embodiment of revolutionary comradeship and sense of obligation, genuine, passionate, ardent and invariable, would help the human beings in our era perfect their personality and provide a key to the display of collectivism. The politico-ideological might of Korean-style socialism will grow stronger than ever before and our motherland will shed its rays as a powerful country in which all the people are united as one in mind when all of them fully display a high sense of moral obligation for the party, the leader, the society, the collective and revolutionary comrades, considering it as ethics and morality and the principle of their activities to live and struggle as required by collectivism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Love and dedication to the socialist motherland is a bounden duty and sense of obligation for the Korean people.

Round-table Talks Held between Korean, German Lawmakers
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 30 (KCNA) -- Round-table talks between deputies to the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly and members of the Bundestag of Germany were held at the Mansudae Assembly Hall today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Deputy to the SPA Ri Jong Hyok, chairman of the DPRK-German Parliamentary Friendship Group, deputies Hong Son Ok, Pak Kyu Hong and others, and members of the visiting delegation of the Bundestag of Germany led by its Member Hartmut Koschyk, chairman of the German-DPRK Parliamentary Friendship Group, and German Ambassador to the DPRK Friedrich Ludwig Loehr. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They exchanged views on developing the relations between the law-making bodies of the two countries and a series of matters of bilateral concern.

Seminar of Social Scientists Marks Anniversary of Pochonbo Battle
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 30 (KCNA) -- A seminar of social scientists was held on May 30 to mark the 70th anniversary of the victory in the Pochonbo battle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In June Juche 26 (1937) President Kim Il Sung advanced into the homeland, leading a large unit of the Korean People's Revolutionary Army and shot a signal flare lighting the nocturnal sky over Pochonbo, ordering its members to wipe out the enemy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The seminar heard five papers which explained and proved the immortal exploit the President performed by leading the Pochonbo battle to victory and its significance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Candidate Academician, Prof. and Dr. Thae Hyong Chol, president of the Academy of Social Sciences, Associate Prof. and Master of Social Science Jo Chol, vice-president of Kim Il Sung University, and other speakers said that the Pochonbo battle was a big event that assured the nation of its resurrection and the victory of the anti-Japanese armed struggle under the banner of Songun and a battle that demonstrated to the world the extraordinary military strategy and Juche-oriented commanding art of Kim Il Sung and shattered the myth of the Japanese imperialists' "mightiness." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They stressed that the battle served as a victorious banner encouraging the Korean people in their anti-Japanese struggle and indicated the path to be followed by the world revolutionary people in their efforts to achieve independence by themselves with arms of revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Present at the seminar were Choe Thae Bok, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, officials in the fields of science, education, party cadre training institutions and the preservation of the revolutionary sites and others.

S. Korean Military Warmongers' Military Provocations Warned
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 30 (KCNA) -- The servicepersons of the Korean People's Army are following with a high degree of vigilance the military provocations of the south Korean military warmongers and will take due measures if they persist in such actions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The KPA Navy Command warned this in a press release issued on May 30 in connection with the fact that the warmongers of the south Korean armed forces perpetrated such a grave military provocation as intruding a group of warships deep into the territorial waters off the West coast of the north side on the same day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 According to the press release, at around 11:20 on Wednesday the warmongers of the south Korean armed forces infiltrated seven warships deep into the territorial waters of the north side southwest of Ssanggyo-ri, Kangryong County, South Hwanghae Province and at around 7:45 and at around 10:40 two warships into the same waters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When the north side demanded over walkie-talkie their immediate withdrawal for the purpose of preventing the situation from deteriorating, they went the lengths of making such bellicose remarks as "they would fire" and "they would punish".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is a serious military provocation creating a touch-and-go situation in those waters and an intolerable challenge to the high degree of patience and self-restraint exercised by KPA servicepersons, the press release noted, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reckless military provocations of the above-said warmongers pushed the situation in the waters off the West coast to such an extreme pitch of tension that a new armed clash may break out there any moment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They would be well advised to properly understand the gravity of the situation and behave with discretion.

Rodong Sinmun denuncia injusta politica de doble rasero de EE.UU.
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 30 de mayo (ATCC) -- En un comentario individual difundido este miercoles, el diario Rodong Sinmun insiste en que Estados Unidos debe retirar la injusta pauta de doble rasero y la politica hostil a la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea, si esta interesado de verdad en la solucion del problema nuclear y de misiles. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Ultimamente, EE.UU. intensifica sus maniobras para ultimar los preparativos para la guerra nuclear y estrechar la connivencia militar con Japon, precisa el comentarista y prosigue: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En particular, partiendo de su politica de doble rasero, EE.UU. permite en silencio y hasta respalda la conversion de Japon en una potencia militar y el establecimiento del Sistema Antimisiles por parte de los reaccionarios de este pais. Lo mismo sucede en el problema de posesion de armas nucleares por Israel y otros paises. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al contrario, el problema nuclear de la RPDC surgio por la amenaza nuclear de EE.UU. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Si el imperio no hubiera acentuado la amenaza a la RPDC con artefactos nucleares, ni habria flotado ese diferendo entre ambas partes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Entonces, la conducta de EE.UU., que mide con diferentes varas el armamento nuclear de algunos paises como Israel y el desarrollo de armas nucleares para la autodefensa por parte de la RPDC, muestra su doble cara y su politica unilateralmente hostil a esta. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Nunca son criticados EE.UU., Japon y otros paises que fabrican a su antojo las armas nucleares sofisticadas y los misiles de proxima generacion. Pero si surgen problemas cuando la RPDC toma una medida destinada a fortalecer sus fuerzas para la defensa legitima. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Mientras EE.UU. y otros paises empleen esta inadmisible pauta de doble rasero, nunca sera posible resolver correcta e imparcialmente el problema nuclear y de misiles y  resultaran invalidos cualquier derecho o tratado internacionales.

Rodong Sinmun fustiga intento de Japon de ingresar en TPI
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 30 de mayo (ATCC) -- La intencion de Japon de tomar parte en las actividades del Tribunal Penal Internacional, que trata los crimenes de lesa humanidad como el exterminio masivo y la agresion, deviene una burla e insulto a la conciencia de la humanidad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Asi senala el periodico Rodong Sinmun en un comentario individual de este miercoles y continua: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En los ultimos dias, Japon trata de aprovechar taimadamente las restricciones del estatuto de la citada entidad, que define ejercer el poder judicial solo a los crimenes del siglo XXI, con el proposito de encubrir sus peores crimenes antieticos, que nunca existieron ni existiran en la historia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Por lo tanto, las pretensiones del pais isleno de afiliarse al TPI resultan un colofon de sus maniobras encaminadas a evadir la liquidacion del pasado criminal. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Si bien Japon actua equivocadamente para comprar el permiso al ingreso a esa entidad internacional y sus puestos importantes como el cargo de juez, debe darse cuenta de que el dinero no es un remedio omnipotente. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   No habra otra cosa tan ridicula y absurda si este pais criminal de guerra, inmoral y falto de la conciencia logra adquirir la potestad de enjuiciar en ese organo los crimenes de lesa humanidad en virtud del derecho internacional. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Aunque Japon se vista de seda, no podra ocultar las huellas del criminal. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  No se debe permitir jamas que los crimenes ensangrentados de Japon fueran lavados por los organismos internacionales como el Tribunal Penal Internacional. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Japon tiene que expiar primero sus crimenes del pasado contra la humanidad para comenzar de nuevo, antes de hablar de la "paz" y el "dominio de la ley".
